.TH TDOC 1 "January 2026" "TDOC 1.0.0" "Termux Utilities"
.SH NAME
tdoc \- Termux Doctor, system diagnostic and repair tool for Termux

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tdoc
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBTDOC\fR (Termux Doctor) is a diagnostic, reporting, and repair tool
designed specifically for the Termux environment.

It performs system scans, validates repositories, checks core tools
(Python, NodeJS, Git), reports system status, and provides guided or
automatic fixes when issues are detected.

TDOC is designed to be:
.IP \[bu] 2
Safe (read-only by default)
.IP \[bu]
Termux-packages compliant
.IP \[bu]
Scriptable (JSON output supported)

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Run a full system scan and display a human-readable status report.
This is the default command.

.TP
.B scan
Run system checks and update internal state without displaying
the full status report.

.TP
.B version
Display TDOC version, codename, and build date.

.TP
.B explain
Explain detected issues using AI-assisted diagnostics.

.TP
.B fix
Attempt to fix detected issues interactively.

.TP
.B fix --preview
Show what actions would be performed without making changes.

.TP
.B fix --auto
Automatically apply all safe fixes without prompting.

.TP
.B report
Print the raw system state file generated by the scan process.

.TP
.B doctor --json
Output full diagnostic data in JSON format.

.TP
.B security
Analyze Termux repository security and configuration.

.TP
.B security --json
Output repository security analysis in JSON format.

.TP
.B update
Show instructions for updating TDOC via the Termux package manager.

.TP
.B help
Display a short usage summary.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR --json
Output data in JSON format (supported by some commands).

.SH FILES
.TP
.I $PREFIX/lib/tdoc/
TDOC core library directory.

.TP
.I $PREFIX/lib/tdoc/data/state.env
System scan state file.

.TP
.I $PREFIX/bin/tdoc
TDOC executable.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.

.TP
.B 1
Command error or invalid usage.

.TP
.B 127
TDOC installation corrupted or missing core files.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TDOC_ROOT
Overrides the default TDOC installation directory.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run a full system status check:
.B
tdoc status

.TP
Get system diagnostics in JSON:
.B
tdoc doctor --json

.TP
Preview automatic fixes:
.B
tdoc fix --preview

.SH SECURITY
TDOC does not collect telemetry and does not transmit data.
All analysis is performed locally unless explicitly configured otherwise.

.SH COMPATIBILITY
TDOC is designed for:
.IP \[bu] 2
Termux (Android)
.IP \[bu]
Android 8+
.IP \[bu]
ARM, ARM64, x86_64 architectures

